Improve the Performance and Scalability of LWR Sites with Experience Delivery (Pilot)

Boost the performance and scalability of your LWR sites using Experience Delivery, a powerful new infrastructure for hosting LWR sites. Along with subsecond page load times, this new infrastructure provides improved security and search engine optimization to ensure that your site meets your customers' demands.

Where: This change applies to LWR sites accessed through Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions.

NOTE: This feature is not generally available and is being piloted with certain Customers subject to additional terms and conditions. It may be discontinued at any time and may never become generally available.

Why: Existing LWR sites use client-side rendering, meaning that all the HTML, JavaScript, CSS, and assets are downloaded to the client before being rendered in the browser.

Experience Delivery uses server-side rendering and a dedicated content delivery network to render the page on the server and then cache it in the CDN. This approach provides optimal site performance with page load times up to 60% faster.

Since the previous release, we added support for enhanced domains, custom URLs with path prefixes, and custom URLs containing only root URLs were previously allowed.

How: To participate in this pilot, contact your Salesforce account executive. After your org is approved for the pilot, you can enable Experience Delivery at the site level in the Settings tab of the site's Administration workspace.
title: Improving Performance with Experience Delivery
